{"name":"Birth of the Cruel","type":"skill","img":"systems/fabulaultima/assets/icons/shambling-zombie.svg","system":{"class":"Necromancer","schemaVersion":"1.01","notes":"<p>When a non-<strong>Villain </strong>NPC you can see that belongs to the <strong>beast, humanoid, monster,</strong> or <strong>plant </strong>Species dies, you may spend 2 Grave Points and <strong>reduce your maximum Hit Points and Mind Points</strong> by an amount equal to that NPC's <strong>level</strong>. If you do, their corpse becomes a <strong>Minion </strong>who obeys your telepathic commands:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Its <strong>Species </strong>becomes <strong>undead </strong>and it receives all <strong>undead rules</strong>. The new Affinities to <strong>dark, light</strong>, and <strong>poison </strong>overwrite any preexisting Affinity, but the original Species' rules are otherwise <strong>maintained</strong>.</li>\n<li>Its <strong>Rank </strong>becomes <strong>soldier</strong>; if the original creature was an <strong>elite </strong>or <strong>champion</strong>, the GM must reduce the Minion's HP and MP accordingly.</li>\n<li>The newly created Minion is a completely new creature and has full HP, full MP, and no status effects. It retains the original creature's <strong>equipment</strong>.</li>\n<li>Your Minion takes its own turn during conflicts, and the Game Master must count it as an <strong>additional Player Character</strong> when designing a conflict.</li>\n<li>When you <strong>rest</strong>, your Minion also gains the full benefits of resting.</li>\n<li>If your Minion is reduced to 0 Hit Points, if you are <strong>more than 1 travel day</strong> away from it, or if you die or fall unconscious, your Minion is immediately <strong>destroyed</strong>.</li>\n<li>You may also destroy your Minion<strong> at any time</strong>; if you want to create a new Minion, you must first destroy the current one.</li>\n<li>If your Minion is destroyed, your maximum HP and MP scores <strong>return to normal</strong>.</li>\n</ul>","hasLevels":false,"skillLevel":{"value":0,"max":0},"isHeroic":true,"requirements":"<p>You must have mastered the Necromancer Class.</p>"},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jqXkiXaQTTrIXvYj":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rLsK56j55XboB7Xl"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"fabulaultima","systemVersion":"0.6.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1684982972370,"modifiedTime":1684985092251,"lastModifiedBy":"jqXkiXaQTTrIXvYj"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"P1RKZrQWKxImwRPR"}
{"name":"My Trust in You","type":"skill","img":"systems/fabulaultima/assets/icons/prayer.svg","system":{"class":"Orator","schemaVersion":"1.03","notes":"<p>After another Player Character who is able to hear you performs a Check, you may spend 1 Fabula Point and invoke one of their <strong>Traits </strong>or <strong>Bonds </strong>in order to let them reroll dice or improve the Result of the Check (following the normal rules). Then, if you have a <strong>Bond </strong>towards that character, they recover <strong>[SL x 10]</strong> Mind Points.</p>","hasLevels":true,"skillLevel":{"value":1,"max":2},"isHeroic":false,"requirements":""},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jqXkiXaQTTrIXvYj":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.A8H8AzI69zoxjtYM"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"fabulaultima","systemVersion":"0.6.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685066979698,"modifiedTime":1685067675086,"lastModifiedBy":"jqXkiXaQTTrIXvYj"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"Pxin2IOl72iLcWdK"}
{"name":"Painful Lesson","type":"skill","img":"systems/fabulaultima/assets/icons/cut-palm.svg","system":{"class":"Darkblade","schemaVersion":"1.01","notes":"<p>After another creature causes you to lose Hit Points (with an attack, a spell or any other method), you may immediately perform the <strong>Study </strong>action on that creature for free. If you do, gain a bonus equal to <strong>[SL]</strong> to your Check.</p>\n<p>Remember, you can study the same aspect of a creature only once.</p>","hasLevels":true,"skillLevel":{"value":1,"max":3},"isHeroic":false},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jqXkiXaQTTrIXvYj":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.dJLqDzdLliGYrNmG"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"fabulaultima","systemVersion":"0.6.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1684979084762,"modifiedTime":1684979853122,"lastModifiedBy":"jqXkiXaQTTrIXvYj"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"QgzZbBlANudFvV0m"}
{"name":"Heroic Companion","type":"skill","img":"systems/fabulaultima/assets/icons/griffin-symbol.svg","system":{"class":"Wayfarer","schemaVersion":"1.03","notes":"<p>Your bond with your companion grows stronger. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The companion's maximum Hit Points increase by 10.</li>\n<li>Choose one of the companion's Attributes: <strong>Dexterity, Insight, Might,</strong> or <strong>Willpower</strong>. The chosen attribute is permanently increased by one die size (up to a maximum size of <strong>d12</strong>).</li>\n<li>The companion gains an additional Skill. When you reach level <strong>40</strong>, or if you have already reached it, the companion gains an additional Skill. Make sure to discuss your Skill choices with the Game Master and other Players.</li>\n</ul>","hasLevels":false,"skillLevel":{"value":1,"max":1},"isHeroic":true,"requirements":"<p>You must have mastered the <strong>Wayfarer </strong>Class, and must have acquired the <em><strong>Faithful Companion</strong></em> Skill.</p>"},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jqXkiXaQTTrIXvYj":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.2Ni0BZJkqkMSIoK7"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"fabulaultima","systemVersion":"0.6.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685142454869,"modifiedTime":1685149714530,"lastModifiedBy":"jqXkiXaQTTrIXvYj"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"QyXmBtfrlYGteIdU"}
{"name":"Healing Power","type":"skill","img":"systems/fabulaultima/assets/icons/healing.svg","system":{"class":"Spiritist","schemaVersion":"1.03","notes":"<p>When you cast a spell that targets one or more allies, if you have an <strong>arcane </strong>weapon equipped, you may have each of those allies recover an amount of Hit Points equal to <strong>[SL, multiplied by the number of Bonds you have]</strong>.</p>\n<p>This healing is separate from any healing caused by the effects of the spell.</p>","hasLevels":true,"skillLevel":{"value":1,"max":2},"isHeroic":false,"requirements":""},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jqXkiXaQTTrIXvYj":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z24593STX0P9uzpt"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"fabulaultima","systemVersion":"0.6.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685072503414,"modifiedTime":1685072652924,"lastModifiedBy":"jqXkiXaQTTrIXvYj"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"RGBuadd8o3zktoaD"}
{"name":"Spellblade","type":"skill","img":"systems/fabulaultima/assets/icons/lightning-saber.svg","system":{"class":"Elementalist","schemaVersion":"1.01","notes":"<p>When you cast an offensive spell targeting <strong>a single creature</strong>, if the spell has a <strong>total Mind Point cost of [SL x 10] or lower</strong> and you have one or more <strong>bow</strong>, <strong>brawling</strong>, <strong>dagger</strong>, <strong>flail</strong>, <strong>spear</strong>, or <strong>sword </strong>weapons equipped, you may choose one of those weapons. If you do, your Magic Check for the spell will use the chosen weapon's Accuracy Check formula.</p>","hasLevels":true,"skillLevel":{"value":0,"max":4},"isHeroic":false},"effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"jqXkiXaQTTrIXvYj":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.dmBcKKAw51DBVH8l"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"fabulaultima","systemVersion":"0.4.8","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679123668161,"modifiedTime":1679124099960,"lastModifiedBy":"jqXkiXaQTTrIXvYj"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"S7RUp9QnAwpTnpLs"}
